# Pushable AI — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Multi-tenant AI Employee platform. Two apps in a monorepo:
- `apps/web` — Next.js 15 + shadcn/ui (Vercel)
- `apps/server` — Fastify + LangGraph JS (Contabo)
- `packages/db` — Drizzle schema + migrations (shared)
- `packages/types` — Shared TypeScript types

## General Rules
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere. No `any`. Ever.
- No unused imports, no unused variables.
- No `console.log` in production code. Use a logger utility.
- Every file must have a single clear responsibility.
- Never put business logic in API route handlers. Route → Service → DB.
- Never hardcode strings. Use constants files.
- All secrets come from environment variables only.

## Naming Conventions
- Files: `kebab-case.ts`
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Functions/variables: `camelCase`
- DB tables: `snake_case`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- Zod schemas: `[entity]Schema` (e.g. `createAgentSchema`)
- Types/Interfaces: `PascalCase` with no `I` prefix

## Folder Structure Rules
- All API route logic lives in `services/`, not in the route file itself
- All DB queries live in `repositories/`, called only from services
- All shared types live in `packages/types`
- All Drizzle schema lives in `packages/db/schema/`
- One file per DB table in schema folder
- Components go in `components/[module]/` — never dump in root components

## Database Rules (CRITICAL)
- Every query MUST be scoped by `workspaceId`. No exceptions.
- Never query without RLS or explicit workspace filter.
- All DB operations go through repository functions. No raw SQL in routes or services.
- Migrations via `drizzle-kit` only. Never manually alter tables.
- Every table must have: `id`, `workspaceId`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`

## API Rules (apps/server)
- All routes follow REST: GET/POST/PUT/DELETE
- All request bodies validated with Zod before touching the DB
- All responses follow `{ data, error, meta }` shape
- HTTP errors use proper status codes — never return 200 with error inside
- Auth middleware runs on every protected route

## Frontend Rules (apps/web)
- Use shadcn/ui components. Never write custom UI from scratch if shadcn has it.
- Server components by default. Add `"use client"` only when necessary.
- All API calls go through `lib/api/` client functions. No raw fetch in components.
- All forms use `react-hook-form` + Zod resolver.
- No inline styles. Tailwind only.
- Loading states and error states are mandatory for every async component.

## LangGraph Rules
- Each agent run gets its own thread ID derived from `sessionId`
- All graph definitions live in `apps/server/src/graphs/`
- Checkpointer is always Postgres-based (never in-memory)
- Tool definitions live in `apps/server/src/tools/`
- Never call LangGraph directly from Next.js — always via passthrough proxy

## Error Handling
- All async functions wrapped in try/catch
- Services throw typed errors (create custom error classes)
- Routes catch and return appropriate HTTP status
- Frontend shows toast on error using sonner

## Git Rules
- Commit messages: `type(scope): message` — e.g. `feat(agents): add tool assignment`
- Types: feat, fix, chore, refactor, docs
- Never commit `.env` files
- One feature = one commit (don't mix concerns)
